entry.title: 2019 Team Zoot Camp
entry.summary:
Vendor: Giddy Up Multisport
Type: camp
Price: 299.00

Inaugural Team ZOOT Spring Training Camp, presented by GiddyUp Multisport!! 

Dates: Wednesday, March 13th- Sunday, March 17th

Got the "winter blues"? Excited to be part of Team Zoot? Want swim, bike and run in Southern California? Want to be part of the first Team ZOOT camp?  Tried of the trainer? Treadmill?  The Team ZOOT Training camp will be sure to get you ready for the 2019 season. The main goal for camp is for you to have FUN while taking away something that helps you have the best season you can and to get to know your fellow Team ZOOT members!  We are excited to have multiple Ironman champion Ben Hoffman, he will be here training right along side of you and feels that-"Even though the tendency is to think of Ironman Professionals as a different breed, there are so many commonalities between the pros and amateur athletes! We all strive for self-improvement, seek community, have bad days, make mistakes, and thrive on challenge. Join the discussion to learn and share some of the essential tools learned in the commitment of racing, and hear what I focus on to achieve some of my best performances."  Coach Michellie Jones, Ironman World Champion, Olympic Silver Medalist, Xterra World Champion and Giddyup Coach will be joining Ben Wednesday night (and, if we are lucky she'll bring her Olympic medals) 

Please keep in mind: Camp is FUN!!  The work we will be doing will focus on is to help each of you grow as athletes and not to pound you with mileage (you can do that at home!). Our goal is that each camper leaves camp with something that helps them improve in the swim, bike and run and along the way learn a more in-depth appreciation for all your sponsors and have a great time with your fellow Team ZOOT members!

Team ZOOT Spring Camp: $299
Register before February 15th save $50 use code EARLYBIRD

If you have any questions, please reach out to Coach Robin

 

Email:     coachrobospin13@gmail.com

Cell:        760.402.7626

**All dinners are optional and you will be responsible for two dinners**

Retul bike fitting: We are lucky to have expert Retul bike fitter Nate Koch available through out the week and is offering fitting to all of Team Zoot.

Nate's philosophy is: "Speed is a byproduct of comfort and sustainability. We want to understand how your body functions most optimal and allow it to do that naturally. It is when the body is forced into positions and made to do unnatural movements that discomfort and injuries occur. The only pain you should feel on the bike is the pain you inflict upon yourself. Your saddle should feel great majority of the time, nothing should be going numb and you shouldn’t have any neck, back,  shoulder or knee pain."  After five years of bike fitting and several thousand bike fit I have learned not just how to use a fancy motion capture machine, but more importantly what changes to make when riders express certain issues. When your body shifts forward, back or up and down it is trying to tell us where it wants to be and we just have to know how to listen.

Nate's Retul bike fitting rate is normally $325- Team Zoot rate $225.  To schedule a fitting please email Nate at actasif@gmail.com.

To pay for a Retul bike fit: PayPal: actasif@gmail.com

Support: ALL the sessions are fully supported. Rides will be sagged with nutrition, hydration, mechanical support and directions.

Weather: Yes, SoCal is beautiful this time of year but it still is a high desert, so can be chilly mornings and cool evenings.  Be prepared for both warm and cold weather. Pack you thermal cycling jacket, base-layer, gloves, arm and knees warmers.  

FAQ’s:

 

-Can I attend if I am new to the team:

Of course-one of the many purposes is to met and get to know other teams members no matter what your skill level is.

-Can I rent a bike?

Yes, we have several bike shop locally that will rent you a bike BUT we don encourage that you bring your bike. And, Canyon will have some demos for you to try.

-Do I need a rental car?

We do encourage that you do rent a car, campers are responsible for their own transportation to and from the airport, as well as, team functions.

-Can I send my bike prior to camp?  Yes, we will have a bike mechanic.  The charge to have your bike built and then boxed after the week is $180.  If you want to ship your bike, we suggest Bike Flights and shipped directly to the shop. Please email us for further information.

-Can we purchase ZOOT clothing during the week!  YES!  We will have several meeting points at ZOOT HQ and will have the store all to yourself.

entry.summary:

Monthly Coaching | Michellie Jones

Head Coach Michellie Jones

Michellie Jones's most impressive talents are not just found in her accolades that includes Olympic Medals, Ironman World Championship Titles and ITU World Championships but in her unique ability and vast experience to access goals and provide all the ingredients required to be successful.

A former professional athlete who coaches, guides and empowers each athlete to optimum athletic and personal success. A vast knowledge of triathlon rules, regulations, injury prevention and motivational techniques with over 30 years participating and coaching at the Elite Level in Triathlons. The coaching philosophy is directed towards cultivating hardworking, focused athletes and teams with an emphasis on teamwork, perseverance and inspiring athletes to do their best. Dream it. Believe it. Live it.

Giddy Up Coaching 

  • Startup interview and assessment
  • Evaluation of current state of fitness
  • Individual goal development and pace of progression
  • Custom programming based on your needs, strengths and weaknesses
  • Unlimited communication by phone, text, email
  • Weekly video or phone calls
  • The training program and plan development
  • Skills assessment sessions for swim, bike and run
  • Developing an annual training plan
